%h1 SAML IDp
%p The rails SAML Identity Provider app implements the server side of SAML authentication. It  acts as an IdP (Identity Provider) using the SAML v2.0 protocol. It provides a means for managing authentication requests and confirmation responses for SPs (Service Providers).

%p= link_to 'Sign up', signup_path

%hr
= link_to 'Sign in', signin_path

%h4 Registered Users
%ul
  - @users.each do |user|
    %li
      = link_to user.email, user
      - if user.signed_in?
        %span.online Online since #{user.current_logged_in_at.localtime}

